Rating: 2
Easy and foolproof but too sweet. Also, the orange flavor was overwhelming even though I used far less zest than the recipe called for. Next time, I would reduce the amount of sugar, use just a splash of orange liquor and a few ribbons of zest for a more delicate flavor. Agree with the reviewer who stated it needed to be strained but disagree with the reviewer who used brown sugar to caramalize the top. Brown sugar does not caramalize well. It goes straight from being moist granular sugar to being little black burnt beads with no caramalization stage in between.

