Rating: 3
this was a very good dish however, it did not have a strong enough orange flavor. actually, instead of using orange zest, take the zest from an entire orange and squeeze the oil from the zest and add that instead, that way the brulee isn't gritty with the zest. also don't just use the small amount of grand marnier they suggest. just dump some in and taste it. that's what i did and it came out great.

Rating: 4
This is the best Creme Brulee! I did strain it before pouring into ramikins. It was then heavenly smooth! Also, if you put a cloth in the bottom of the pan before you fill it with water, the cups will not slip and slid. I used brown sugar for the tops and put them under the broiler just before serving, so that the top was warm and the inside was cool and smooth. The family raved!

